13:51.891 --> 13:54.676
- Abed, stop!
- Okay.

13:54.711 --> 13:56.541
Keep rolling.

14:09.448 --> 14:11.066
Hello?
Hello.

14:11.100 --> 14:13.451
Hello?

14:20.259 --> 14:24.379
Hello, it's me.
Luis Guzman.

14:24.413 --> 14:26.247
- Hello!
- Hi.

14:26.282 --> 14:30.602
Hi, Mr. Guzman,
Dean/Director Craig Pelton.

14:30.636 --> 14:33.054
Sorry, I've been editing.

14:33.088 --> 14:34.305
It's a ltle bit of a mess.

14:36.442 --> 14:38.092
What the --  is that?

14:38.110 --> 14:39.761
Oh, that's a possum.

14:39.779 --> 14:41.095
Once you spend
some time with them,

14:41.113 --> 14:45.867
you see they're just like
big, gentle rats.

14:45.901 --> 14:48.203
- Who's the guy?
- I'm no one.

14:48.237 --> 14:50.321
That's Abed.
He's a little bit odd.

14:50.373 --> 14:52.774
Now, without further ado,

14:52.808 --> 14:56.494
here is the commercial
you will be staring in.

14:59.482 --> 15:00.665
Why do I go Greendale?

15:06.338 --> 15:08.757
- Aah!
- What's in the box?

15:08.791 --> 15:10.825
Ohh...Oh...

15:13.863 --> 15:15.764
I've got to make a phone call.

15:15.798 --> 15:18.850
I had to tell this dean
I couldn't do his commercial.

15:18.901 --> 15:20.902
He didn't take that
too well either.

15:20.936 --> 15:22.470
Y'all gotta help this dude.

15:22.505 --> 15:23.822
I mean, aren't you his friends?

15:23.856 --> 15:25.940
I'm more of a fly on the wall.

15:25.974 --> 15:27.826
What is go--

15:27.860 --> 15:29.360
what?

15:29.412 --> 15:31.579
You won't be in my commercial,

15:31.614 --> 15:33.832
but you'll be in
his stupid documentary?

15:33.866 --> 15:35.650
All he does
is follow people around.

15:35.668 --> 15:37.619
Yeah, but haven't you seen
<i>Hearts of Darkness?</i>

15:37.653 --> 15:39.037
- Way better than--
- I want you

15:39.088 --> 15:41.423
the hell off of my campus,
you ungrateful backstabber.

15:41.457 --> 15:42.874
I already got rid
of your trailer.

15:42.925 --> 15:44.125
I had a trailer?

15:44.159 --> 15:46.044
Can anyone hear me?

15:46.095 --> 15:48.379
I will walk off
this production.

15:48.431 --> 15:51.015
I will quit!
Hello?

15:51.050 --> 15:53.017
I come here to shoot
this commercial for Greendale.

15:53.052 --> 15:54.836
That's what you had
written on the script.

15:54.854 --> 15:56.337
Ugh, that script was terrible.

15:56.355 --> 15:57.388
I thought it was pretty good.

15:57.440 --> 15:58.673
Of course you'd think that.

15:58.691 --> 16:00.275
You went here.

16:03.446 --> 16:06.231
Oh, I get it.

16:06.282 --> 16:09.016
You're worse than crazy.

16:09.034 --> 16:10.685
You're ashamed of your school.

16:10.719 --> 16:13.187
And that--that statue
of me out there,

16:13.205 --> 16:14.188
that's just wrong, man.

16:14.206 --> 16:15.623
Well, the bronze
adds ten pounds.

16:15.658 --> 16:17.358
- Nah, man--
- It's not going to be perfect.

16:17.376 --> 16:19.026
Screw you.

16:19.044 --> 16:21.963
I'm just saying, don't worship
the people leaving Greendale.

16:21.997 --> 16:23.998
Worship the people
that are here.

16:24.032 --> 16:27.585
Worship this place.
It changes people's life.

16:27.636 --> 16:30.672
Look, I loved my time here.
I got laid like crazy.

16:30.706 --> 16:32.807
That's way before
<i>Boogie Nights</i> too.

16:32.842 --> 16:36.911
Look, this is a special school.

16:40.149 --> 16:42.383
You don't deserve to be here.

16:49.057 --> 16:50.525
Are you still filming, Abed?

16:50.559 --> 16:52.076
Yeah, but try not
to address me.

16:52.111 --> 16:55.113
I'm not really here.

16:55.164 --> 16:57.582
Neither am I.

16:57.616 --> 17:01.736
I don't think I can finish
my commercial.

17:01.754 --> 17:04.405
But I think I know
how your documentary ends.

17:08.511 --> 17:10.044
Hi, I'm Craig Pelton,

17:10.078 --> 17:12.297
Dean of Greendale
Community College.

17:14.349 --> 17:16.550
I have failed this school.

17:16.585 --> 17:18.303
I have failed it
because I thought

17:18.354 --> 17:20.722
I was better than Greendale.

17:20.756 --> 17:23.107
See, I went to a university,

17:23.142 --> 17:26.310
so I thought it was my job
to improve this place.

17:26.362 --> 17:28.646
But it turns out that the only
thing wrong with Greendale

17:28.697 --> 17:30.899
is that it's run by
an insecure wreck

17:30.933 --> 17:33.968
who holds five dances
and two talent shows a year

17:34.003 --> 17:36.204
because he's afraid that
the school isn't good enough.

17:38.157 --> 17:39.607
But Greendale is good enough

17:39.642 --> 17:41.776
because it accepts me
for what I'm not.

17:41.794 --> 17:44.979
Greendale is the best school
in the entire world,

17:45.014 --> 17:49.517
and I'm so sorry
what I've done to it.

17:49.552 --> 17:51.786
And I'm sorry what I've done
to the ice cream machine.

17:51.804 --> 17:54.472
Aah!

17:54.506 --> 17:59.327
Please, no one eat out of it
until you clean the nozzles.

17:59.361 --> 18:01.829
The janitor knows how.

18:03.332 --> 18:04.632
I'm horrible.

18:05.734 --> 18:07.135
I'm horrible.

18:09.305 --> 18:11.272
Gentlemen, what I'm about
to show you

18:11.307 --> 18:13.775
is not the commercial
you paid me to create.

18:13.809 --> 18:15.026
What I am about to show you

18:15.077 --> 18:16.778
is a glimpse into
my mind and soul.

18:16.812 --> 18:18.780
Please hold your questions
until the end.

18:18.814 --> 18:20.481
I know you will have
a lot of them,

18:20.516 --> 18:23.818
but I'll understand
if you'd rather I just leave.

18:28.173 --> 18:29.791
Why do I go Greendale?

18:29.825 --> 18:31.709
The dean is a genius.

18:31.760 --> 18:33.294
To meet different people.

18:33.328 --> 18:34.712
With three kids at home,

18:34.763 --> 18:36.831
you better believe
every penny counts.

18:36.849 --> 18:39.634
I loved my time here.
I got laid like crazy.

18:39.668 --> 18:40.885
So why should you--

18:40.936 --> 18:42.053
Why should you--

18:42.104 --> 18:44.505
Why should you
go to Greendale?

18:44.540 --> 18:48.059
Greendale is the best school
in the entire world.

18:49.211 --> 18:51.746
Go Greendale,
go Greendale, go!

18:53.882 --> 18:54.899
It's good.

18:54.950 --> 18:55.984
Y-you know what,
better than good.

18:56.018 --> 18:57.201
Good enough.

18:57.236 --> 18:59.821
Is there any more
of the crazy Chinese guy?

18:59.855 --> 19:01.322
He pops.

19:01.356 --> 19:03.207
I'm confused.
That's not my commercial.

19:03.242 --> 19:04.742
I-I didn't make that.

19:04.793 --> 19:07.028
Yeah, yeah, okay, Zemeckis,
it moved through you.

19:07.062 --> 19:09.197
Anyway, congratulations.

19:09.231 --> 19:11.549
That should last us
another 16 years.

19:11.583 --> 19:13.501
So, uh, what's next?

19:13.535 --> 19:16.471
- Chump's rusty bucket?
- Quarter taps.

19:21.760 --> 19:23.344
- Did you do this?
- You did mostly.

19:23.378 --> 19:25.179
You got the footage
you needed on the first day.

19:25.213 --> 19:29.851
I added a little bit of
my footage to fill in the gaps.

19:29.885 --> 19:32.420
I thought you were
a fly on the wall.

19:32.454 --> 19:34.422
Some flies are too awesome
for the wall.

19:34.456 --> 19:36.424
Documentarians are supposed
to be objective,

19:36.458 --> 19:38.426
to avoid having
any effect on the story.

19:38.460 --> 19:40.361
And yet we have more effect
than anyone.

19:40.396 --> 19:41.729
Because we decide to tell it.

19:41.764 --> 19:43.114
And we decide how it ends.

19:43.165 --> 19:44.666
Will your story be
yet another sad one

19:44.700 --> 19:46.701
of yet another man
who just wanted to be happy?

19:46.735 --> 19:49.671
Or will your story acknowledge
the very nature of stories

19:49.705 --> 19:51.706
and embrace the fact
that sharing the sad ones

19:51.740 --> 19:53.074
can sometimes make them happy?

19:53.092 --> 19:54.592
Ugh.

19:54.626 --> 19:57.879
Before you say anything...

19:57.913 --> 19:59.263
Nope, I've got nothing.

19:59.298 --> 20:01.182
Can you just forgive me?

20:05.921 --> 20:07.438
Yep.

20:07.473 --> 20:09.757
Why?

20:09.775 --> 20:12.643
Because we've all been there.

20:12.695 --> 20:14.779
Which is why we're all here.

20:19.368 --> 20:23.104
Aww!

20:23.122 --> 20:24.489
I'm a good Dean?

20:24.540 --> 20:26.958
Yeah.

20:26.992 --> 20:31.079
Can someone help me get
a live possum out of my office?

20:31.113 --> 20:32.246
We could do that.

20:32.280 --> 20:35.299
It just keeps jumping
and skittering.

20:35.334 --> 20:38.119
And you think you're prepared,
and then it skitters again.

20:39.955 --> 20:41.122
Okay, scene's over.

20:41.140 --> 20:42.757
Hmm?

